#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
archguard – aggressive security auditing & hardening for Arch Linux
version 3.0.0

Modular, reversible hardening plus deep-scan audit suite.
Every change is backed up, checksummed, and logged. Every audit
produces a timestamped report. Nothing is silent.

THREAT MODEL: Personal workstation requiring high assurance. Assumes
the user is willing to review findings and accept potential breakage.
NOT for production servers without careful testing. Will install
additional packages (rkhunter, lynis, aide, clamav, nmap …) when
--install-deps is passed.

WHAT'S FIXED vs v2:
  - subprocess results checked on all critical paths; stderr logged on failure
  - _interrupted reset per-apply; no cross-module bleed
  - LogAudit uses journalctl -g (grep) correctly
  - ArchSecurity does proper version comparison via pyalpm / vercmp
  - AIDE move protected with existence check + error handling
  - ClamAV infected-count parsing wrapped in try/except
  - NetworkAudit nmap gets -T4 + timeout flag + configurable ports
  - ArchSecurity results cached to /var/cache/archguard/ with 1h TTL
  - All bare except Exception replaced with specific types + logged
  - import re at top level
  - Structured subprocess helper run_cmd() used everywhere
  - New modules: SSHAudit, SudoAudit, CronAudit, WorldWritable,
    SuidAudit, OpenVulnScan, SecureBoot, DnsLeakCheck, TimeSyncAudit

Usage:
  sudo archguard apply firewall --profile workstation
  sudo archguard apply --preset hardened --verify
       archguard audit rkhunter --install-deps
       archguard audit --preset full_audit
       archguard status
       archguard report          # unified HTML/text report
       archguard revert firewall
       archguard backups --days 7
"""

